Launching an Amazon EC2 Instance

all services -> compute -> EC2 -> instances -> launch instance

From here you can pick which server you want. There is also a market place and community configured instances.

next -> 

From here you can choose how many instances you want

add storage -> next

Now we can configure the security group, name your group and apply a description

review and launch -> launch

Then we have to create a key pair. This is used to actually access your instance.

It has a public and private key. The public key is held by AWS and the private key is something that you download to authenticate.

Click download key pair -> launch instances





